	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117303"><p>This came up years ago on<nobr> <wbr></nobr>/. and I stopped to look up the papers on losses from<br>a) electricity to microwaves<br>b) loss in transmission<br>c) microwaves to electricity<nobr> <wbr></nobr>...and they add up to over 50%.    So, ground-based loses 75% (dark half the time, and half more lost unless you expensively point the panel at the sun all the time, then there's weather.)</p><p>So, space-based produces 2X as much power for the same acreage of cells.</p><p>If you can launch 100 km^2 into space for the expense of where you were going to put 200 km^2<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

