	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64117353">All that energy coming down will eventually end up as heat on the earth's surface that would not have been there otherwise. The question of how much waste heat such as this contributes to warming today, as opposed to greenhouse gasses, is up for debate at this point. I've seen estimates of 1% to over 50%. Certainly additional heat won't help the problem and my impression is that the heat itself directly and severely affects weather. Beaming energy is a diversion from more effective solutions.</div>
	</div>

